      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"تُرَدُّ اَلْعَمْيَاءُ وَ اَلْبَرْصَاءُ وَ اَلْجَذْمَاءُ وَ اَلْعَرْجَاءُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4497 - Abd al-Hamid narrated from Muhammad ibn Muslim, who said:\nAbu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said: \"A blind woman, a woman with vitiligo, a woman with leprosy, and a lame woman can be returned (marriage contract can be annulled due to these conditions).\""
        ]
      }
    },
